cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with interpretability of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and adversarial example detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new strategy for interpretability using a Bag of visual Word representation within the network, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a generative adversarial network for associating visual and semantic meaning to the codebook elements also falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with adversarial example detection, which falls under the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
